ut for the chance to take down an enemy that I have a vendetta against. The raid went well, however I feel a little cheated.<br>
<br>
I may be posting this in the wrong area, but since this is my first time here, please bear with me.<br>
<br>
Long story short, a Torbrin's Mystical Eyepatch dropped last night. All Wis/Int casters were asked to roll, but when I asked if bards were allowed to, I was vehemently told no. Why? Because &quot;no bard would ever wear this.&quot; (Avante)<br>
<br>
I begged to disagree, but, rather than cause a hold-up and end up ruining others raid experiences, I conceded very quickly. Now, the question remains... why was I not allowed to roll?<br>
<br>
Reasons given:<br>
&quot;No bard would ever wear this.&quot;<br>
Not true. Yes there are better pieces, but if I actually owned this item I would wear it not only for the stat boosts, but the permanent see invisible is very nice as well.<br>
<br>
&quot;Bards don't use mana.&quot;<br>
Not true. Especially now. Our 39 charm can last up to a minute and costs 60 mana to cast. When I am in a group, I often use charm to clear up adds. More mana means more charm ability. <br>
<br>
&quot;Casters deserve this more than a hybrid.&quot;<br>
I know a few Shadowknights, Paladins, Rangers and (for all practical intents and purposes) Beastlords who would disagree with this as well. If this is the reason that is given, I shouldn't play any of these classes at all. And neither should anyone else.<br>
<br>
Look, I'm not trying to cause trouble, and I'm not trying to take the item from someone else. They won the roll and I am VERY happy for them. But to be told that I can't even roll, despite the fact I was tripping over Vox's feet and bleeding for some of the fight, because of all things I'm a bard... well, it makes me not want to even try to help on these occasions. On the whole, the raid was run fairly well for a situation where most of the people didn't know each other at all. We were a team, despite our differences, and we vanquished a mighty foe. It was fun.<br>
<br>
But please... next time... if you bleed, you should be able to roll.<br>
<br>
Lautrec - Bard of the Tribunal - Silver Daggers - Karana  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uqamginenighteagle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qamgine Nighteagle</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.talonswitch.com/q.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#8E9173>(9/16/02 1:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscouncildiscussions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=93.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.talonswitch.com/qamgine.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A little miffed</span><hr size=1> I personally wasn't there, but 7 of my guild members were. They were estatic to be able to attend and for that I thank you.<br>
