<br>
IMHO there are two reasons why this rule has been here.<br>
<br>
1) Quality of use.  While bards, hybrids, tanks, etc. CAN use the item, 98% of the time they wouldn't and they would just sell the item or give it to a guildmate.  On the other hand this is an awesome item for an Intelligence or Wisdom caster, in fact one of the best items you are going to see outside of UBER zones which most of our guilds will never see.  And frankly, as Avante put it, a mask like this without ac is only going to be used by a bard except in very specific circumstances, whereas any caster that wins that item is going to be wearing it permanently, except in very specific circumstances (need for resists or something is all I would be able to think of).<br>
<br>
2) This is one of three items (White Dragon Hide for cloak, and Polished Mithril Mask off of one of the FG's at Nagafen) that are really useful for both Int Casters and Wis Casters.  There are a few other trinkets (cleric hammer, etc) that they can use, but most would be a downgrade in equipment for most people nowadays.  On the other hand bards have 2 epic drops between the dragons, A Horn (Instrument), 2 Haste items, Gauntlets, and various odds and ends that would be upgrades for almost any bard that drop between the two dragons.  Albiet not much dropped last night that bards would be excited about, but there is a lot of stuff that bards would love there.  Now you really need to have your clerics, druids, shamans, enchanters, wizards, necros, and mages there, and without several of those classes being there there is no way you can possibly succeed.  So in this case I think limiting the casters very limited already selection of items that draw them here is bad, especially when there is so much there that is available (and frankly meant for) bards, including 2 items that are completely bard exclusive (the horn and the white scale).  <br>
<br>
Since there has been some confusion about loot rules (even though I have not changed anything except epic availability rules), I will work up a chart of items that can drop and lay down the rules about who can roll for them.  There are only a few where there are limits within the classes/races that can use them, and this just happens to be one of them.  If you read back you can probably find the thread where Haemish was talking about this item (I believe) way back when he was leading the raids. <p>Farrnusno <BR>
Guild Leader <BR>
Souls of the Valiant <BR>
KCoG Dragon Liaison</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uqamginenighteagle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qamgine Nighteagle</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.talonswitch.com/q.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#8E9173>(9/16/02 2:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscouncildiscussions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=93.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.talonswitch.com/qamgine.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A little miffed</span><hr size=1> Well that makes sense. Had no idea that Int/Wis got such limited drops. Thanks for clarifying it. <p>Qamgine Nighteagle<br>
