 <p><center> <img src=http://www.telusplanet.net/public/flarren/LagKommipic.gif> </center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhaemish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haemish</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>KCoG Founder</span><br>  Posts: 732<br> <font color=#8E9173>(9/16/02 2:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscouncildiscussions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=93.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.godwinclients.com/sd/haemish_new.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A little miffed</span><hr size=1> &quot;Lautrec, being from SD you, best of any should know why these rules were set in place, afterall it was your guild that first instated the loot rules still held by CoG.&quot;<br>
<br>
Unfortunately, when I made my break with the Daggers months ago, there isn't a lot said about me and the ideas I put forth in the SD ranks. I'd imagine an astonishing number of the new SD don't even know who I am. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  sadf<br>
<br>
However, as both Farnnusno and Lagdalen said, this is something I instituted in the loot rules a long time ago. Casters get, quite frankly, hosed in terms of the loot off of dragons. Nagafen has I think one item that's worthwhile for casters, 2 if you count Magus Roykl's mask. Vox has a little more for casters, what with the cleric hammer (not a great weapon for clerics), the Rez staff, and the weight reducing packs. And, of course, the eyepatch. Bards get an instrument off of each dragon. Melees in the 40-52 range (and some beyond that) get significant upgrade weapons and armor. Casters are especially necessary on dragon raids, and are often asked to die more than once... on both failed and successful dragon raids, I've known casters who have died in excess of 6 times. And that's without click stick resses. That gets ugly real quick. <br>
<br>
So to give them some incentive, I restricted the rolls on some items. The raid leaders who followed me have kept these traditions up, with some changes that fit with the changes to the game. <br>
<br>
The you bleed you roll principle does apply, but it isn't a unilateral &quot;You're there, you roll.&quot; The raid leader has the option of restricting items as he sees fit, so long as it is announced before hand. I'd imagine most have read the post, so it probably wasn't repeated in a pre-raid briefing. <br>
<br>
Unfortunately, I don't have the option to sticky posts, or I'd sticky the loot rules for specific raids that we have. <br>
<br>
If possible, Farrnusno, could you write up a list of your Dragon raid loot rules? We'll bump it each time a raid comes around.   <p>Haemish MacLennan<br>
Founder<Br>
Karana Council of Guilds<br>
"I don't play role-playing games to be a politician."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ulautrec75.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lautrec75</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#8E9173>(9/16/02 10:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscouncildiscussions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=93.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Still...</span><hr size=1> Again, I'm not trying to cause problems...<br>
<br>
But why &quot;punish&quot; me just because the things that I am used to rolling on don't drop?<br>
<br>
As far as the idea goes that a bard wouldn't wear this, well, it's just absurd. I mean, come on? &quot;Monk-item&quot; is the cry of the equipment message boards. And ideas such as &quot;a bard would never wear this&quot; only spreads the lie. This is a character that I have put alot of time and effort into, and have plans for. My enchanter-suit that I am working on will have some value in the future as it has been stated that when bards are &quot;re-balanced&quot; they are looking at bards as a caster class. Absor even said he always felt that bards were casters. Would I not get to roll on a Flowing Though item, even though those are the only pieces in the game that can help my mana regen besides Alt Advancement? Mark my words, things are going to change for bards and we have to be adaptable.<br>
<br>
I am in a good guild, and, Haemish, I have heard of you. I thank you for starting a guild that is well organized, just and fun. I've been in and out of guilds for quite some time and have never had this much fun. I hope that everyone has a chance to be in a guild like Silver Daggers. <br>
<br>
Again, I am not trying to stir controversy. I'm simply a little miffed that I didn't even get a chance to roll. And was VERY embarrased when I was basically shut down in front of a large group before I even had a chance to state a case. But if I had, it only would have made people angry and made me look like a loot hog. So, my pride is a little hurt, but I'll get over it. I only did this post as food-for-thought. You never know when something like this will happen to you.<br>
