<br>
There are alot of &quot;if's&quot; in the previous posts... &quot;if a bard had gone on all of these raids&quot; &quot;if the bards had a chance to roll&quot;, etc... but I'm talkng about the raid I went on. Not the others. I wasn't aware of these loot rules, as I haven't been on a KCoG raid before and happened to be in Everfrost when there was a call for a Vox raid. But now I see. From now on, unless it has bard listed as a class on the item, I will not roll. ALL/ALL items are obviously not intended for my class, so I'll leave them alone unless I pick them up myself while soloing or adventuring with my group of real life friends. No hard feelings, folks... I'm just a little dissappointed. I figured there would be a little more understanding in the Council. But enough politics. I'm out.<br>
<br>
And, by the way... bard mana is not Charisma based; it's Intelligence. If you don't believe me, please refer to Everquest.com, Allahkazam, EQCasters realm or (if these don't convince you) sign on your bard alternate and have an enchanter cast KEI on you. There's no charisma buff, but the 25 points of Intelligence will definitely knock your mana bar down a little. <br>
<br>
